\limits_{\text{Warm}}^{{I_2}/\text{NaOH}}} }\limits_{(step\,II)} CH{I_3}$$<br><br>Here, N will be <br><br><img src="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hrhphy/a4028a7b-3edb-4f30-a895-b85ac66adaa3/2ef7ff60-3d0c-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hrhphz.png?format=png" data-orsrc="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hrhphy/a4028a7b-3edb-4f30-a895-b85ac66adaa3/2ef7ff60-3d0c-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hrhphz.png" loading="lazy" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh" alt="WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Alcohol and Ether Question 10 English Explanation 1"><br>(IUPAC name = Butan-2-ol)<br><br>Step I It involves the oxidation of secondary alcohol to corresponding alcohol in the presence of K<sub>2</sub>Cr<sub>2</sub>O<sub>7</sub> and H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>.<br><br><img src="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hrkoql/356e622d-b234-4daa-9ae5-2a6bf4c3dcf4/81cf1ed0-3d0c-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hrkoqm.png?format=png" data-orsrc="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hrkoql/356e622d-b234-4daa-9ae5-2a6bf4c3dcf4/81cf1ed0-3d0c-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hrkoqm.png" loading="lazy" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh" alt="WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Alcohol and Ether Question 10 English Explanation 2"><br>Step II It involves the iodoform reaction. Ketone formed in step I have one methyl group linked to the carbonyl atom are oxidised by sodium hypohalite to sodium salts of corresponding carboxylic acids having one carbon atom less than that of carbonyl compound.<br><br><img src="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hrle8h/0e3fe14b-d330-4fda-b5cb-8dd62a165a0b/95813c10-3d0c-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hrle8i.png?format=png" data-orsrc="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hrle8h/0e3fe14b-d330-4fda-b5cb-8dd62a165a0b/95813c10-3d0c-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hrle8i.png" loading="lazy" style="max-width:100%